{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"situational-15000","unitId":"scene-356","title":"常用数字","sectionId":"chapter-16","sectionTitle":"天文地理有规律","pageStart":1731,"pageEnd":1736,"extractionMethod":"text-layer","wordEntryCount":42,"duplicateEntryCount":0,"pages":[{"number":1731,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"356 常用数字"},{"type":"section","text":"Step1 场景词"},{"type":"entry","text":"zero [ˈzɪərəʊ]","headword":"zero"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 零"},{"type":"note","text":"◎zero hour零时"},{"type":"entry","text":"five [faɪv]","headword":"five"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 五"},{"type":"note","text":"◎five pence五便士硬币/give me five击掌"},{"type":"entry","text":"eleven [ɪˈlevn]","headword":"eleven"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 十一"},{"type":"entry","text":"twelve [twelv]","headword":"twelve"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 十二"},{"type":"note","text":"◎twelve disciples 十二门徒"},{"type":"entry","text":"thirteen [ˌθɜːˈtiːn]","headword":"thirteen"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 十三"},{"type":"note","text":"◎the Old Thirteen 美国早期的国旗"},{"type":"entry","text":"fifteen [ˌfɪfˈtiːn]","headword":"fifteen"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 十五"},{"type":"note","text":"◎fifteen all一平（网球比赛专用词）"}]},{"number":1732,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"twenty [ˈtwenti]","headword":"twenty"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 二十"},{"type":"entry","text":"thirty [ˈθɜːti]","headword":"thirty"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 三十"},{"type":"entry","text":"twenty-one [ˌtwenti ˈwʌn]","headword":"twenty-one"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 二十一"},{"type":"entry","text":"ninety [ˈnaɪnti]","headword":"ninety"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 九十"},{"type":"entry","text":"hundred [ˈhʌndrəd]","headword":"hundred"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 一百"},{"type":"note","text":"◎by the hundred（s） 数以百计"},{"type":"entry","text":"a hundred and one 一百零一","headword":"a hundred and one"},{"type":"entry","text":"two hundred 两百","headword":"two hundred"},{"type":"entry","text":"thousand [ˈθaʊznd]","headword":"thousand"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 一千"},{"type":"note","text":"◎a thousand and one 一千零一；无数的"},{"type":"entry","text":"ten thousand 一万","headword":"ten thousand"},{"type":"entry","text":"million [ˈmɪljən]","headword":"million"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 百万"},{"type":"note","text":"◎millions of数百万的…"},{"type":"entry","text":"one in a million极稀有的人或事","headword":"one in a million"}]},{"number":1733,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"billion [ˈbɪljən]","headword":"billion"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 十亿"},{"type":"entry","text":"decimal [ˈdesɪml]","headword":"decimal"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.小数"},{"type":"note","text":"◎decimal point小数点"},{"type":"entry","text":"point [pɔɪnt]","headword":"point"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.点；分数"},{"type":"entry","text":"at all points在各方面/zero point two five 0.25","headword":"at all points"},{"type":"entry","text":"one third 三分之一","headword":"one third"},{"type":"entry","text":"two over five 五分之二","headword":"two over five"},{"type":"entry","text":"five ninths 九分之五","headword":"five ninths"},{"type":"entry","text":"percent [pəˈsent]","headword":"percent"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.百分比"},{"type":"note","text":"◎one hundred percent百分之百；不折不扣"},{"type":"entry","text":"first [fɜːst]","headword":"first"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第一"},{"type":"note","text":"◎first name名"},{"type":"entry","text":"second [ˈsekənd]","headword":"second"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第二"},{"type":"note","text":"◎on second thought再三考虑"},{"type":"entry","text":"third [θɜːd]","headword":"third"}]},{"number":1734,"blocks":[{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第三"},{"type":"note","text":"◎third party第三方"},{"type":"entry","text":"fourth [fɔːθ]","headword":"fourth"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第四"},{"type":"note","text":"◎fourth quarter第四季度"},{"type":"entry","text":"fifth [fɪfθ]","headword":"fifth"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第五"},{"type":"entry","text":"eighth [eɪtθ]","headword":"eighth"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第八"},{"type":"entry","text":"ninth [naɪnθ]","headword":"ninth"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第九"},{"type":"entry","text":"tenth [tenθ]","headword":"tenth"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第十"},{"type":"entry","text":"eleventh [ɪˈlevnθ]","headword":"eleventh"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第十一"},{"type":"note","text":"◎at the eleventh hour最后一刻"},{"type":"entry","text":"twelfth [twelfθ]","headword":"twelfth"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第十二"},{"type":"entry","text":"twenty-first [ˌtwenti ˈfɜːst]","headword":"twenty-first"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第二十一"},{"type":"entry","text":"twenty-second [ˌtwenti ˈsekənd]","headword":"twenty-second"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第二 十二"}]},{"number":1735,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"twenty-third [ˌtwenti ˈθɜːd]","headword":"twenty-third"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第二十三"},{"type":"entry","text":"thirtieth [ˈθɜːtiəθ]","headword":"thirtieth"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第三十"},{"type":"entry","text":"sixty-sixth [ˌsɪksti ˈsɪksθ]","headword":"sixty-sixth"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第六十六"},{"type":"entry","text":"hundredth [ˈhʌndrədθ]","headword":"hundredth"},{"type":"definition","text":"num. 第一百"},{"type":"note","text":"◎hundredth birthday 百岁生日"},{"type":"entry","text":"one hundred and seventh 第一百零七","headword":"one hundred and seventh"},{"type":"section","text":"Step2 学以致用"},{"type":"text","text":"Number 13数字13"},{"type":"text","text":"One of the most widespread superstitions is that thirteen is unlucky,"},{"type":"text","text":"and so general is this idea that many hotels do not have a room number"},{"type":"text","text":"thirteen.Some people will not start a trip on the 13th day of the month,"},{"type":"text","text":"especially if it happens to be a Friday. Various explanations have been"},{"type":"text","text":"given as to the origin of this superstition.The most popular explanation is"},{"type":"text","text":"that there were thirteen persons at the Last Supper, Judas being frequently"},{"type":"example","text":"represented as the thirteenth. The superstition about the number thirteen is"},{"type":"text","text":"universal. We can find it in France, England, throughout almost the whole"},{"type":"text","text":"of Europe, and in America.It has long been a matter of etiquette in France"},{"type":"text","text":"to avoid having exactly thirteen guests at a dinner or party, and the person"},{"type":"text","text":"who is invited to fill the fourteenth seat at the table is usually known as"},{"type":"text","text":"quatorizième."}]},{"number":1736,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"一个广为流传的迷信是13这一数字不吉利。因此一般来说，许多"},{"type":"text","text":"酒店不设13号房间。一些人不愿意在13号出发旅行，如果那天恰逢星"},{"type":"text","text":"期五便更是如此。对这一迷信的来源，可谓众说纷纭。最普遍的说法"},{"type":"text","text":"是“最后的晚餐”中共有13人，出卖耶稣的犹大经常被描画为第13个"},{"type":"text","text":"人。数字13的迷信十分普遍，法国、英国等几乎所有的欧洲国家以及"},{"type":"text","text":"美国都有这种迷信。长久以来，法国的社交礼仪要求避免晚宴或聚会"},{"type":"text","text":"中正好有13位客人出席，而因此被邀请来凑数的食客则被称为“第14"},{"type":"text","text":"个”。"}]}]}